        "created_at": "2020-08-13T05:33:01.540Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Seems closely related to this, though not quite the same:</p><aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"10694\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/ad7895/48.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/option-to-group-chats-create-chat-folders/10694\">Option to *group* chats / create chat folders</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/17\"><span data-category-id=\"17\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #83B72A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category \" title=\"Post your ideas here for new features and functionality for the Signal app.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    I’d like to get the option to create folders. These would just be like current chat/group tabs and their names/background colors would be customizable. \nFor example you could have a folder called “work” which includes all work-related chats with colleagues or “family” including all family members. \nUpdate: \nYou should also be able to set custom notification settings applying for the whole folder (if you get messages from three different persons in a folder, the group would have an indicator show…\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Undercover\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"16184\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/u/ea5d25/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Undercover:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>and the ability to be able to name group chats like in Whatsapp</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Group chats can already be named in Signal. Or does Whatsapp have something specifically different that you would like to see?</p>",
