        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Undercover\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"16184\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/u/ea5d25/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Undercover:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I didn’t know they could</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Have you ever actually used group chats? Signal has had a field for setting the name when creating one for a long time (as well as letting you set a photo for the group), and now setting a name for the group is actually required before you can create it.</p>",
