        "created_at": "2025-12-08T00:16:06.911Z",
        "cooked": "<p>This can be done using chat folders, which is available everywhere except iOS for now, so I’m closing this as a duplicate.</p><aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"10694\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/ad7895/48.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <div class=\"quote-title__text-content\">\n      <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/option-to-group-chats-create-chat-folders/10694\">Option to *group* chats / create chat folders</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/ios-feature-requests/19\"><span data-category-id=\"19\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #2D8B39; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF; --parent-category-badge-color: #83B72A;\" data-parent-category-id=\"17\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category --style-square --has-parent\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">iOS Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    I’d like to get the option to create folders. These would just be like current chat/group tabs and their names/background colors would be customizable. \nFor example you could have a folder called “work” which includes all work-related chats with colleagues or “family” including all family members. \nUpdate: \nYou should also be able to set custom notification settings applying for the whole folder (if you get messages from three different persons in a folder, the group would have an indicator show…\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
